
How to set up an externally modded Java Minecraft server

1. Check out the git repository
  - Go to https://www.eggsquishit.net/
  - Click the GitHub icon (the cat) at the top right
  - Find the "mcserver" repository
  - Follow GitHub's instructions to clone the repository locally

2. Install the Java Minecraft server
  - Create "mc" directory inside your cloned "mcserver" repo
  - Download "server.jar" from the Mojang website
  - Copy server.jar to "mc" directory
  - Run server once inside the "mc" directory:
    $ cd mc
    $ java -Xmx1024M -Xms1024M -jar server.jar nogui
    $ cd ..
  - Edit eula.txt to accept the Minecraft server EULA
  - Edit server.properties

3. Run the python wrapper in the "mcserver" clone
  $ ./runserver.py
